Job Summary
Join Our Innovative Team at Flex Power Modules as a Test Developer!
Are you ready to be part of a groundbreaking company that is transforming the landscape of power solutions for Datacenter, Telecom, and AI applications? At Flex Power Modules, we pride ourselves on developing and producing world-class power modules that are making a global impact. Our cutting-edge products, including DC/DC and PoL (point of load) solutions, are designed to meet the ever-evolving needs of our customers, and we are constantly innovating to stay ahead of the curve.
As we experience unprecedented growth, particularly in the artificial intelligence sector, our Kalmar design center is expanding rapidly. Here, we collaborate with industry leaders to create advanced power modules for their state-of-the-art AI designs. Verification is a critical aspect of our product development, and we are committed to enhancing our testing capabilities. To accelerate our time to market, reduce manual work, and improve test quality, we are investing significantly in automating our testing processes. Our long-term vision is to streamline the journey from test execution to data specification, minimizing time and effort.
We are looking for a passionate Test Developer to join our dynamic software team. In this role, you will have the opportunity to develop innovative software for our diverse testing systems, primarily using Python. You will also work with SQL databases to post test results and help build web interfaces for extracting and generating presentation materials.
As part of a collaborative Agile team of three developers, you will work closely with a team leader who will guide you in your professional growth. This is your chance to make a significant impact in a fast-paced environment while contributing to cutting-edge projects that are shaping the future of technology.
Join us at Flex Power Modules and be a part of a team that is powering the next generation of innovation. Apply now and help us shape the future of technology!
What a typical day looks like:* You will collaborate with your team to align on past achievements and future activities, ensuring everyone is on the same page;
* Actively participate in software team sprint planning sessions;
* Present your accomplishments and insights to various stakeholders, demonstrating the value of your and the team’s contributions;
* Develop frameworks and reporting generators that drive our long-term test automation initiatives, enhancing efficiency and accuracy;
* Collaborate closely with design teams to develop and refine specific test requirements.


The experience we’re looking to add to our team:* A completed degree in software or electronic engineering;
* A few years of hands-on experience in software development;
* Experience in python programming language and database design;
* Familiarity with working in an Agile environment, contributing to a dynamic and collaborative team culture;
* Understanding of measurement techniques and previous experience in the electronics industry is advantageous;
* Fluent Swedish and English, both verbally and in written.


Here is what you’ll get for the great work you provide:* An exciting global organization, working on projects for many well-known brands across different industries;
* A long-term role with many opportunities to learn, grow and develop.


A career at Flex Power Modules offers the opportunity to make a difference and invest in your growth in a respectful, inclusive, and collaborative environment. If you are excited about a role but don't meet every bullet point, we encourage you to apply and join us to create the extraordinary.
Please submit your CV and personal letter in English.
